#. type: multicols*
#: sections/game_modes.tex:10
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Each game of Heroes III is played using a \\textbf{Scenario} from the Mission Book.\n"
"The core game only allows you to choose scenarios for 1-3 players. For 4 or more players, expansions are required.\\par\n"
"In addition to the scenario objectives, read the \\pagelink{End}{general victory conditions} depending on the scenario type.\\par\n"
"There are several types of scenarios:\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/game_modes.tex:14
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\\subsection*{Clash}\n"
"A fully competitive mode.\n"
"Your opponents control Neutral Units in your Combat.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/game_modes.tex:19
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\\subsection*{Campaign}\n"
"A single player mode\\index{Solo Mode} of interconnected Scenarios against an enemy AI.\n"
"For rules unique to Solo Mode, see \\pagelink{AIrules}{the AI rules}.\n"
"Further rules changes are detailed in the Campaign Mission Books.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/game_modes.tex:22
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\\subsection*{Alliance}\n"
"Usually a 2 vs.~2 team-based mode with expanded opportunities to \\pagelink{Trading}{trade} between allied players.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/game_modes.tex:25
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\\subsection*{Cooperative}\n"
"A Cooperative mode where everyone shares the same goal. \\pagelink{AI Units}{The AI rules} and expanded \\pagelink{Trading}{Trading rules} apply here.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/game_modes.tex:28
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\\subsection*{Tournament}\n"
"A 1 vs.~1 mode with different way of building Map and scoring. See the Tournament Book.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/game_modes.tex:32
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"In addition, the \\textbf{Battlefield Expansion} introduces two focused 1 vs.~1 modes without Scenarios (see the expansion's rulebook):\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/game_modes.tex:35
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\\subsubsection*{Adventure}\n"
"The Map exploration is replaced with Adventure Cards, culminating in a tactical combat on a large hexagonal battlefield.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/game_modes.tex:38
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\\subsubsection*{Skirmish}\n"
"Skip the exploration phase and engage directly in tactical combat.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

